  "title": "Therapy Aide #SGUnitedJobs",
  "description": "<p><u>Clinical Care</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist the Therapists in providing appropriate therapy treatments (includes lifting, transferring and transporting patients)</li>\n  <li>Assisting the therapists (occupational therapist and physiotherapist) in assessment, treatment plan development and progress review</li>\n  <li>Evaluate, monitor and review treatment on a regular basis to document needs and progress of residents and ensure that treatment is appropriate and effective.</li>\n  <li>Conducting group therapeutic exercises/activities and individualised rehabilitation treatment under the supervision of the therapists.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Quality</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Participate as a member of the health team via attending relevant ward rounds, meetings and team conferences, and involved in discussion of resident-related issues (e.g. updates on resident’s progress) with caregivers and family members.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that all equipment and therapy tools are in good condition and working order.</li>\n  <li>Keep proper inventory of and maintain all therapy equipment and fixtures by regular servicing and replacement of equipment.</li>\n  <li>Maintain self-development through continuing education.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Training &amp; Development</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Guide, supervise and train caregivers and volunteers on their performance of duties (including scheduling) and implementation of social and recreational activities for the residents.</li>\n  <li>Provide training for caregivers in preparation for resident’s discharge back into home environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Locally Trained</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>GCE N Level</li>\n  <li>Attained Training in either one of the courses:<br>\nWSQ Higher Certificate / Advanced Certificate / in Healthcare Support (Nursing Care)<br>\nInstitute of Technical Education (ITE) Approved Training Centre (ATC) Healthcare (Home Care) Programme</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Successful applicants without the qualifications will be sent for Certificate in Community Care (Community Care Traineeship Programme) with all courses funded by the employer.</p>",
